TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Gas Transmission Problem Solved by an Extension of the Simplex Algorithm
AU  - De Wolf, Daniel
AU  - Smeers, Yves
Y1  - 2000/11/01
PY  - 2000
DA  - 2000/11/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.46.11.1454.12087
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.46.11.1454.12087
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1454
EP  - 1465
VL  - 46
IS  - 11
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The problem of distributing gas through a network of pipelines is formulated as a cost minimization subject to nonlinear flow-pressure relations, material balances, and pressure bounds. The solution method is based on piecewise linear approximations of the nonlinear flow-pressure relations. The approximated problem is solved by an extension of the Simplex method. The solution method is tested on real-world data and compared with alternative solution methods.
AB  - The problem of distributing gas through a network of pipelines is formulated as a cost minimization subject to nonlinear flow-pressure relations, material balances, and pressure bounds. The solution method is based on piecewise linear approximations of the nonlinear flow-pressure relations. The approximated problem is solved by an extension of the Simplex method. The solution method is tested on real-world data and compared with alternative solution methods.
